Gross Salary: S$8000 - S$10000
Location: Singapore
Job Description:
• Evaluate and implement nursing / operational strategies to deliver optimal care.
• Promote teamwork and provide leadership.
• Plan and set nursing goals and objectives in consultatioin with the team.
• Evaluate and plan the objectives accordingly the operational and financial aspects/targets.
• Evaluate and omprove the work processes and practices.
• Ensure the clinical policies and standard of procedure are in line.
• Conduct patient and staff rounds to promote satisfaction levels.
Requirement:
• At least Bachelor's Degree in Nursing.
• Valid Singapore Nursing Board License.
• Must have managerial experience for at least 3 to 5 years in a hospital setting.
• Strong engagement, operational and managerial skills in leading teams.
• Ability to identify improvement opportunities and drive continuous improvement in the hospital.
• Good verbal communication skills with the ability to engage and work well with different stakeholder.
